    <bibl><title>L'Italia</title>,
<date when="1900-12-15">December 15, 1900</date><title level="a">THE MONUMENT TO GARIBALDI</title></bibl>
   </div>
  </front>
  <body>
   <p>The sketches of the Garibaldi monuments to be erected in Chicago, have arrived, and whoever is interested in seeing them, may attend the dance and reception given by the United Societies at the North Side Turner Hall, December 22, when the monuments will be unveiled to the public.</p>
   <p>The united societies are: "Unione e Fratellanza", "Legione C. Garibaldi". "Christoforo Colomba", and the "Liguria".</p>
   <p>The monument will stand in Lincoln Park, and the execution of it was entrusted to the sculptor, M. V. Gherardi.</p>
